==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homeric
<hw>Ho*mer"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Homericus</ets>, Gr. <grk>"Omhriko`s</grk>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to <persfn>Homer</persfn>, the most famous of Greek poets;
resembling the poetry of Homer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Homeric verse</b></col>, <cd>hexameter verse; -- so
called because used by Homer in his epics.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homesick</ent>⟦br⟧
